==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ordonnance
<hw>Or"don*nance</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. See
<er>Ordinance</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Fine Arts)</fld> <def>The disposition
of the parts of any composition with regard to one another and the
whole.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Their dramatic <qex>ordonnance</qex> of the parts.</q>
<rj><qau>Coleridge.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ordonnant</ent>⟦br⟧
